[{"Code":"en","Title":"Viettel Pay","Slug":"viettal-pay","ContentType":2,"Content":"<p data-block-id=\"70b29582-5ce0-490f-afed-528e6d6a18e0\"><img data-block-id=\"6472b6eb-7a3b-4bc2-845c-b2774bae6e2d\" src=\"https://cdn.document360.io/217abc43-8677-41fb-a81d-fceeb1fa0358/Images/Documentation/image(74).png\" class=\"adv-wysiwyg-img\" mediatype=\"img\" alt=\"\" title=\"image(74).png\" width=\"184\" height=\"70\" dataalign=\"left\" datadisplay=\"flex\" data-type=\"media-content\" fixaspectratio=\"false\" autoaspectratio=\"true\" shadow=\"no\" border=\"no\" round=\"no\" link=\"\" newtab=\"\" style=\"width:184px;height:70px;\"></p><p data-block-id=\"0e6b3804-528a-42ff-891f-07bcbcc86fb0\">Viettel Pay was launched by Viettel Group, one of Vietnam’s largest telecommunications companies, as a digital payment platform in 2018. Designed to provide accessible financial services, it offers features such as bill payments, money transfers, mobile top-ups, and QR code payments. Viettel Pay supports both online and offline transactions, catering to users in urban and rural areas alike.</p><p data-block-id=\"2b5798d6-dff0-43ee-a024-1e95b1ab51a8\" class=\"p1\">Leveraging Viettel’s extensive network and reputation, Viettel Pay has rapidly gained a large user base. Its integration with government services and partnerships with merchants nationwide have further cemented its position as a trusted and versatile digital payment solution in Vietnam.</p><hr class=\"hr-divider1\"><h2 data-block-id=\"6146dcc6-4245-4158-a034-de0971f8c50b\">Features</h2><div data-type=\"table-content\"><table width=\"926\" class=\"editor360-table\" borderstyle=\"solid\" style=\"max-width:926px;width:926px;\"><colgroup><col style=\"width:463px;\"><col style=\"width:250px;\"></colgroup><tbody><tr><td colspan=\"1\" rowspan=\"1\" colwidth=\"463\" style=\"overflow:hidden;padding:2px 3px 2px 3px;vertical-align:bottom;\"><p data-block-id=\"402452f7-7a96-45f3-856a-beec3466fb7a\">Channel Code</p></td><td colspan=\"1\" row